summary: Completed comprehensive testing of The Booker appointment scheduling platform. Frontend works perfectly, but critical backend Entity Framework bug prevents tenant creation and blocks entire booking flow.

critical_bugs.issue: Entity Framework domain model error: 'Cannot save instance of Tenant.BusinessHours#BusinessHours.Monday#DaySchedule because it is an owned entity without any reference to its owner'
critical_bugs.impact: Blocks all tenant creation, preventing entire booking flow from working
critical_bugs.error_details: Owned entities (DaySchedule for each day of the week) are being tracked separately instead of as part of the Tenant aggregate. This is a domain modeling configuration issue in Entity Framework.

integration_issues.issue: React error boundary triggered when backend returns 520 error
integration_issues.details: Frontend correctly calls API but doesn't gracefully handle 520 server errors. Shows React error boundary instead of user-friendly error message.

passed_tests: API health check endpoint responds correctly
Booking wizard UI renders properly with step indicators
Admin dashboard loads and displays all management cards
Create tenant dialog opens and form fields work
Navigation between booking and admin pages works
React app builds and runs without JavaScript errors
All UI components have proper data-testid attributes for testing

success_percentage.backend: 20% (2/10 endpoints working - health check and get tenants only)
success_percentage.frontend: 95% (UI fully functional, minor error handling issue)
success_percentage.integration: 0% (Cannot test booking flow due to backend tenant creation failure)

action_item_for_main_agent: CRITICAL: Fix Entity Framework domain model configuration for Tenant.BusinessHours owned entities. The BusinessHours value object and its DaySchedule owned entities are not properly configured, causing 'owned entity without reference to owner' error. This blocks all tenant creation and the entire booking flow. Also improve frontend error handling for 520 server errors.
